{
  "texts": [
    "(16)The enhanced observation features f ′ Ot = {f ′ Ot,n } No n=1 are finally utilized for action decision.",
    "Contrastive Loss.",
    "For improving the modality alignment and encouraging the enhanced observation feature f ′ Ot,n to be more discriminative for facilitating action decision, we introduce a contrastive loss L ct.",
    "Through L ct, we enforce the observation feature f Ot,n to be close with the paired corrected landmark feature f Ut,n while far away from the non-paired corrected landmark feature f Ut,n = {f Ut,j } (1 ≤ j ≤ N o and j ̸ = n).",
    "L ct is composed of two losses L o→u ct and L u→o ct. We calculate L o→u ct by:L o→u ct = - t,n log( e sim(f O t,n,f U t,n)/τ e sim(f O t,n,f U t,n)/τ + f U t,n e sim(f O t,n,f U t,n)/τ),(17)where sim(•, •) denotes the similarity computation, which is the dot product between two features."
  ]
}